Let it ride with a cap, not with a rarity restriction.

A Common/Uncommon-only rule is clean on paper, but it kills a lot of the fun fantasy of “my favourite is the nastiest thing in the store.” Since you want 60% fun / 40% balance, I would preserve that fantasy and only stop the true outliers.

My instinct

Use:

Favourite throw bonus = ×1.5 CL, but capped at +30 CL gained from favourite

So the formula is effectively:

Favourite Bonus Damage = min(Base CL × 0.5, 30)
Final Favourite CL = Base CL + Favourite Bonus Damage

Examples:

Tomato (6 CL) → 9 CL
Burger (12 CL) → 18 CL
Mapo Tofu (38 CL) → 57 CL
Lobster Bisque (45 CL) → 67.5 CL
Million Dollar Steak (70 CL) → 100 CL, not 105

That does a few good things:

It keeps favourite feeling strong on almost everything.

It preserves the emotional fun of “this is my signature weapon.”

It prevents high-end dishes from becoming too silly too often.

It also keeps the bonus readable. Players can learn:
“Favourite usually means about 50% more, unless it’s already huge.”

Why cap beats rarity-lock

A rarity lock creates weird edge cases:

Why can my favourite burger get boosted but not my favourite wagyu burger?
Why does the system stop rewarding me once I like cooler foods?
It makes the rule less intuitive.

A cap is much cleaner:

one rule
all foods eligible
extreme cases controlled

That fits Chompers better.

Why I would not fully “just let it ride”

Because in your current ecosystem, a huge hit is not just damage. It also causes:

100% trigger
inventory drop
movement debuff
possible snowball loot swing
bathroom pressure

So a “one-shot” in Chompers is more like a full momentum theft, not just burst. That is where balance starts mattering.

For a 60/40 fun game, one-shots should exist as hype moments, not become a stable optimal play pattern.

Best version of the mechanic

I’d write it like this:

Favourite Food — Final Version
Your chosen favourite deals ×1.5 CL
The bonus damage from this effect is capped at +30 CL
Self-consuming your favourite applies ×1.5 buff duration
Enemy hits you with your own favourite cause ×2 FL spike

That gives favourite three identities:

offensive signature
support/sustain enhancer
funny vulnerability mirror

That’s richer than the current Craving-only version.

One more thing to watch

If you do this, I would not stack favourite ×1.5 with Craving ×1.5 as separate multipliers. That gets ugly fast.

Instead, make it:

either
Favourite passive throw bonus
or
Craving system

Not both.

Between the two, I think your proposed favourite system is stronger and cleaner than Craving.

My recommendation

Pick this:

Hard cap, no rarity restriction.
That is the most Chompers answer.
